parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unstable Braking Performance in Snowy Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to pull to one side when applying the brakes in snowy conditions can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side when applying the brakes in snowy conditions
making it difficult to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Noisy front brake pads can be a sign of worn-out or damaged brake components, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: coming from the front brake pads when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misadjustment of fuel injector timing can cause the engine to lose power, leading to reduced vehicle performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially causing stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Oil Leak due to Seam Split
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A seam split in the engine can cause an oil leak, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing engine failure.

A transmission cooler line leak can cause the transmission to fail, leading to sudden loss of power, stalling, or inability to shift gears, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission fluid leaking from the cooler line
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent airbag warning light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to the failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard comes on intermittently
the airbag warning light stays on constantly
the airbag system malfunction warning message appears on the dashboard display.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The detachment of welds on the A-frame attachment can cause the A-frame to drop to the ground, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The right front A-frame drops to the ground
unusual noises or vibrations while driving
